```
:::

# Try It Yourself: FizzBuzz

A classic practice problem: print numbers 1 to 15, but for multiples of 3 print "Fizz", multiples of 5 print "Buzz", and multiples of both print "FizzBuzz".

:::try
```js
for (let i = 1; i <= 15; i++) {
  if (i % 15 === 0) console.log("FizzBuzz");
  else if (i % 3 === 0) console.log("Fizz");
  else if (i % 5 === 0) console.log("Buzz");
  else console.log(i);
}
```
:::

Try changing the range or the rules once it works — then mark this lesson complete to finish the course.
